headline: Health insurers remove executive bios, images from websites after UnitedHealthcare CEO killing
summary: UnitedHealth, Elevance and some BCBS plans have deleted senior leadership pages from their corporate sites, while Centene and CVS scrubbed images of their executives online.

headline: Clues Left by a Killer Echo Widespread Anger at Health Insurers
summary: The words “deny,” “defend” and “depose,” written on the bullets found at the scene, have been a rallying cry among many upset with insurance companies.

headline: CENTENE CORPORATION TO HOST VIRTUAL INVESTOR DAY ON DECEMBER 12, 2024
summary: Centene Corporation (NYSE: CNC), a leading healthcare enterprise committed to helping people live healthier lives, today announced that, in the wake of the tragic loss of UnitedHealthcare's CEO Brian Thompson, Centene's Investor Day will now be hosted virtually. The program will be webcast during the previously scheduled date and time – Thursday, December 12, 2024, starting at 8:30 a.m. Eastern Time.
